BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 25 KYODO -- South Korea Monday [25 
April] welcomed the election of Tsutomu Hata as Japan's new 
prime minister and expressed hope that friendly bilateral 
relations will further develop. 
  Foreign Ministry spokesman Chang Ki-ho said the South Korean 
Government expects ties with Japan to reach a new level based on 
common ideas and values. 
  "We are also grateful to the government of former Prime 
Minister Morihiro Hosokawa for the efforts it made for the 
development of Seoul-Tokyo relations," the spokesman added. 

